Miryalkar, Ashok 1:11 PM
Welcome

***************WKAB_NOTRIGGER **************

Just so you're clear on it.  The things in this bypass triggers folder are to be run using a special ID WKAB_NOTRIGGER.  It's pretty straightforward - just.
 
1) Do the regular build
2) After the "run_after.ksh", report to John that the regular build is complete and you're kicking off the NOTRIGGER scripts.  They can continue with the rest of the build and checkout.
3) With SQLPlus, log on with the WKAB_NOTRIGGER login and run these scripts as you would any other one-off.  Spool the output to a file so you can review later.
 
The thing that is special here is that the triggers now have code built in so that triggers won't fire when you are logged in as WKAB_NOTRIGGER.  That allows us to do long-running scripts this way while the rest of the build continues.
 
Mike



**************************************************************************

*********Floradev Examples on how to delploy stuff*************************


Execute $DataRepository/ReleaseBuilds/2009_Aug_Release.1/Database/Schema/create_datarep_tables_010.sql 
 within the DRWKAB schema located in the DRQES1 and DRQA01 databases.

 Compile $DataRepository/ReleaseBuilds/2009_Aug_Release.1/Database/Packages/pkg_Boeing_Feeds.pck 
 within the DRWKAB schema located within the DRQES1 and DRQA01 





**** This how I did ************


Log to Floradev Server

. $SETUPENV DRQES1


FTP FIles over: /workability/DRQES1/SourceSafe


mkdir run_20090729

cd /workability/DRQES1/SourceSafe/run_20090729



sqlplus drwkab/ drwkab_drqes1

spool run_create_datarep_tables_010.lst
@/workability/DRQES1/SourceSafe/2009_Aug_Release.1/Database/Schema/create_datarep_tables_010.sql

spool off

cd /workability/DRQES1/SourceSafe/2009_Aug_Release.1/Database/Packages
spool run_pkg_Boeing_Feeds.lst
@/workability/DRQES1/SourceSafe/2009_Aug_Release.1/Database/Packages/pkg_Boeing_Feeds.pck
spool off



. $SETUPENV DRQA01


FTP FIles over: /workability/DRQA01/SourceSafe

mkdir run_20090729

cd /workability/DRQA01/SourceSafe/run_20090729 



sqlplus drwkab/ drwkab_drqa01

spool run_create_datarep_tables_010.lst
@/workability/DRQA01/SourceSafe/2009_Aug_Release.1/Database/Schema/create_datarep_tables_010.sql

spool off

cd /workability/DRQA01/SourceSafe/2009_Aug_Release.1/Database/Packages
spool run_pkg_Boeing_Feeds.lst
@/workability/DRQA01/SourceSafe/2009_Aug_Release.1/Database/Packages/pkg_Boeing_Feeds.pck
spool off


************** This is how to do *******************************************

1. Get latest stuff from VSS to local

2. FTP files over to for each database. DRQA01 example here : /workability/DRQA01/SourceSafe

3. After that Directory will be created: /workability/DRQA01/SourceSafe/2009_Aug_Release.1/Database/Schema
                                         /workability/DRQA01/SourceSafe/2009_Aug_Release.1/Database/Packages

4. cd /workability/DRQA01/SourceSafe

   --Copy last run_YYYYMMDD directory into new one
    cp -R run_20090722 run_20090729

  
5. vi build_list.dat

   2009_Aug_Release.1

6. ./create_run_sql.ksh


7. This will create run.sql and run.dat. Remove some stuff if needed

8. Login to sqlplus as drwkab/drwkab_SID and @run.sql

   (    EMPLOYEE_ID NUMBER NOT NULL,

)

To fix contact John Mananing and ADA who worked on this table. ADA gave me script to run.

-- RADAR 14542 : Add columns to t_mda_icd9 table

-- Adding new Column BHU_CLAIM_FLAG

ALTER TABLE t_mda_icd9 ADD BHU_CLAIM_FLAG NUMBER(1);



-- Add Comments to column

comment on column T_MDA_ICD9.BHU_CLAIM_FLAG is 'Flag for BHU Claim Type';



ALTER TABLE t_mda_icd9 ADD RESTRICTED_CODES NUMBER;



comment on column T_MDA_ICD9.RESTRICTED_CODES is 'If Flag is 1 then ICDCode is Flagged as Restricted';



-----

--cpt table

ALTER TABLE T_CPT ADD RESTRICTED_CODES NUMBER;



comment on column T_CPT.RESTRICTED_CODES is 'If Flag is 1 then CptCode is Flagged as Restricted';

re run : ./run_qa3.ksh

IMP-00058: ORACLE error 904 encountered

*******************************************************

Based on what I see it because of double quotes 

UPDATE T_PR_QUESTIONS SET EDIT_DATE=SYSDATE, QUESTION_TEXT = 'Based on the provided documentation, and telephonic consultation, when applicable, provide a detailed description of the claimant''s functional impairments, if any, from MM/DD/YYYY through,MM/DD/YYYY.'
WHERE ORDER_ID=1 and PRODUCT_ID in (6002,6003); --QUESTION_ID IN (1005,1040)
COMMIT;



../WKB_2011.Nov.56.68/Scripts/Radar16044_Update_T_PR_Questions.sql
========================================

WHERE ORDER_ID=1 and PRODUCT_ID in (6002,6003); --QUESTION_ID IN (1005,1040)
                                              *
ERROR at line 2:
ORA-00911: invalid character



How to fix it:

sqlplus 
wkab10/wkab10_wkabqa3 

UPDATE T_PR_QUESTIONS SET EDIT_DATE=SYSDATE, QUESTION_TEXT = 'Based on the provided documentation, and telephonic consultation, when applicable, provide a detailed description of the claimant''s functional impairments, if any, from MM/DD/YYYY through,MM/DD/YYYY.'
WHERE ORDER_ID=1 and PRODUCT_ID in (6002,6003); 
COMMIT;

UPDATE T_PR_QUESTIONS SET EDIT_DATE=SYSDATE,QUESTION_TEXT = 'Based on the provided documentation, and telephonic consultation, when applicable, are there any physical or cognitive examination findings of any functional impairment suggesting that the claimant''s ability to work has been directly impacted by an adverse medication effect during the time period from MM/DD/YYYY through MM/DD/YYYY. Please explain.'
WHERE ORDER_ID=2 and PRODUCT_ID in (6002,6003);
COMMIT;

UPDATE T_PR_QUESTIONS SET EDIT_DATE=SYSDATE,QUESTION_TEXT = 'Based on the review of the provided documentation, and telephonic consultation, when applicable, please outline the restrictions and/or limitations imposed by the treating provider(s) and advise in your professional judgment whether they are supported by the medical evidence.'
WHERE ORDER_ID=3 and PRODUCT_ID in (6002,6003);
COMMIT;

UPDATE T_PR_QUESTIONS SET EDIT_DATE=SYSDATE,QUESTION_TEXT = 'Based on the provided documentation, and telephonic consultation, when applicable, please estimate the physical demand level (PDL) of work (i.e. Sedentary, Light, Medium, Heavy, Very Heavy) that the claimant can likely perform from MM/DD/YYYY through MM/DD/YYYY. Please explain.'
WHERE ORDER_ID=4 and PRODUCT_ID in (6002,6003);
COMMIT;

UPDATE T_PR_QUESTIONS SET EDIT_DATE=SYSDATE,QUESTION_TEXT = '(For Core Team Claims ONLY): If the level of impairment indicated in the medical records you reviewed does not support the claimant''s functional inability to perform the duties of his/her job, what type of additional clinical documentation from the treating providers and/or facilities would be helpful for the continued evaluation of the functional impairment asserted by this claimant?'
WHERE ORDER_ID=5 and PRODUCT_ID in (6002,6003);
COMMIT;

******************Assigned Database Support Request #33311239 for RAMPAL

DRQES1, DRSTG


Request Details 
  
*Support Needed: Migrate Object 
*Object Name(s): pkg_Boeing_Medstat.pck

  That fixed it.
  set sqlblanklines on
  sqlplus doesn't like blank lines because of the way it works with batches
  so you have to tell it that blank lines in the middle of a sql statement are OK
  so I put "set sqlblanklines on" at the beginning of the script and "set sqlblanklines off" at the end and re-ran.
  The output is in x.lst in the build directory

set sqlblanklines on
....

set sqlblanklines off

CONSTRAINT fk_ECHOSIGN_TASKINSTANCE_USAGE

CREATE TABLE T_WKAB_ECHOSIGN_USAGE
(
    ECHOSIGN_INSTANCE_ID NUMBER(9,0)     NULL,
    ASSOCIATEDKETYPE_LID NUMBER(9,0)     NULL,
    ASSOCIATEDKEY_ID     NUMBER(9,0)     NULL,
    TASK_INSTANCE_ID     NUMBER(9,0)     NULL
)
ORGANIZATION HEAP
TABLESPACE WKAB_DATA
LOGGING
PCTFREE 10
PCTUSED 0
INITRANS 1
MAXTRANS 255
STORAGE(BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT)
NOPARALLEL
NOCACHE
NOROWDEPENDENCIES
/
ALTER TABLE T_WKAB_ECHOSIGN_USAGE
    ADD CONSTRAINT FK_ECHOSIGN_INSTANCE_USAGE
    FOREIGN KEY (ECHOSIGN_INSTANCE_ID)
    REFERENCES T_ECHOSIGN_INSTANCE (ECHOSIGN_INSTANCE_ID)
    ENABLE
    VALIDATE
/
ALTER TABLE T_WKAB_ECHOSIGN_USAGE
    ADD CONSTRAINT FK_ECHOSIGN_TASKINSTANCE_USAGE
    FOREIGN KEY (TASK_INSTANCE_ID)
    REFERENCES WKAB10.T_TASK_INSTANCE (TASK_INSTANCE_ID)
    ENABLE
    VALIDATE
/

******************* Request for Database Support #47253748 for GARCIA

Xt?r2jdU


stress test

sqlplus 

wkab10
wkab10_wkabstrs


set verify off
set echo on
spool run1.lst
@OracleUpdates20140815.sql
quit



1.	On atnam1p, create a folder called reports_<YYYYMMDD> (you substitute the right date) under /workability/home/oracle/SourceSafe

   cd /workability/home/oracle/SourceSafe
   mkdir run_reports_20140814

2.	From ClearCase or from the e-mail they send, extract the scripts to a local folder on your box.

3.	FTP the files over to the folder you created on atnam1p (I use Exceed Host Explorer FTP so I can just drag and drop).  

4.	Open a terminal window to atnam1p and cd to /workability/home/oracle/SourceSafe/reports_<YYYYMMDD>
5.	Log on with sqlplus as wkab10.  If you need the wkab10 password, its under $ORACLE_BASE/.wkab10.pw

      sqlplus
      wkab10/wscirmnap8t


6.	They usually specify the desired order of the scripts in the e-mail, but if not, you can ask.  It is usually like the one below.  To run the scripts do:


set verify off
set echo on
spool run1.lst
@OracleUpdates20140815.sql
quit
7.	Vi run1.lst and check the output.  If there are errors, forward to Giovanni to look at and wait before running the rest.



8.	Once any issues are resolved run the rest.  It is usually just the two scripts for report rights and widgets.  Those are the same each time so they should run without error.  So connect again with sqlplus as wkab10 and run like below.  Note, the scripts dont usually contain the / to execute the pl/sql block so I do that manually.

 sqlplus
      wkab10/wscirmnap8t

set verify off
set echo on
spool run2.lst
@ADD_NEW_Report_RIGHTS.sql
/
REM -- If no error then run the next one
@ADD_NEW_WIDGET_RIGHTS.sql
/
9.	If these run successfully (and they usually do) then youre all done.

*******************Request for Database Support #47456254 for GARCIA


S1r#H9By


stress test

sqlplus 

wkab10
wkab10_wkabstrs


set verify off
set echo on
spool run1.lst
@OracleUpdates20140829.sql
quit



1.	On atnam1p, create a folder called reports_<YYYYMMDD> (you substitute the right date) under /workability/home/oracle/SourceSafe

   cd /workability/home/oracle/SourceSafe
   mkdir run_reports_20140828

2.	From ClearCase or from the e-mail they send, extract the scripts to a local folder on your box.

3.	FTP the files over to the folder you created on atnam1p (I use Exceed Host Explorer FTP so I can just drag and drop).  

4.	Open a terminal window to atnam1p and cd to /workability/home/oracle/SourceSafe/reports_<YYYYMMDD>
5.	Log on with sqlplus as wkab10.  If you need the wkab10 password, its under $ORACLE_BASE/.wkab10.pw

      sqlplus
      wkab10/wscirmnap8t


6.	They usually specify the desired order of the scripts in the e-mail, but if not, you can ask.  It is usually like the one below.  To run the scripts do:


set verify off
set echo on
spool run1.lst
@OracleUpdates20140829.sql
quit
7.	Vi run1.lst and check the output.  If there are errors, forward to Giovanni to look at and wait before running the rest.



8.	Once any issues are resolved run the rest.  It is usually just the two scripts for report rights and widgets.  Those are the same each time so they should run without error.  So connect again with sqlplus as wkab10 and run like below.  Note, the scripts dont usually contain the / to execute the pl/sql block so I do that manually.

 sqlplus
      wkab10/wscirmnap8t

set verify off
set echo on
spool run2.lst
@ADD_NEW_Report_RIGHTSbetween2000ad3000.sql
/
REM -- If no error then run the next one
@ADD_NEW_WIDGET_RIGHTS.sql
/
9.	If these run successfully (and they usually do) then youre all done.

************************Request for Database Support #49158139 for RAMPAL

Please create table "kns_ivr_w2_dates" owned by user "ivr" in disability IVR production database instance IVPR01. The table exists in IVDV01 and just needs to be duplicated in IVPR01.

Login to DBArtisan with system

CREATE TABLE IVR.KNS_IVR_W2_DATES
(
    W2_START_DATE         VARCHAR2(8) NOT NULL,
    PROVIDER_START_DATE   VARCHAR2(8) NOT NULL,
    TEN99_START_DATE      VARCHAR2(8) NOT NULL,
    POSTSEASON_START_DATE VARCHAR2(8) NOT NULL
)
ORGANIZATION HEAP
TABLESPACE USER_DATA
LOGGING
PCTFREE 10
PCTUSED 0
INITRANS 1
MAXTRANS 255
STORAGE(BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT)
NOPARALLEL
NOCACHE
NOROWDEPENDENCIES
/



GRANT DELETE ON IVR.KNS_IVR_W2_DATES TO APP_DATA_ICAT_ROLE
/
GRANT INSERT ON IVR.KNS_IVR_W2_DATES TO APP_DATA_ICAT_ROLE
/
GRANT SELECT ON IVR.KNS_IVR_W2_DATES TO APP_DATA_ICAT_ROLE
/
GRANT UPDATE ON IVR.KNS_IVR_W2_DATES TO APP_DATA_ICAT_ROLE
/
GRANT SELECT ON IVR.KNS_IVR_W2_DATES TO IVR_SELECT
/

************** ivpr01 *********

CREATE TABLE IVR.KNS_IVR_BOEING_DATES
(
    BLACKOUT_START_DATE      VARCHAR2(8)     NULL,
    BLACKOUT_START_TIME      VARCHAR2(4)     NULL,
    POST_BLACKOUT_START_DATE VARCHAR2(8)     NULL,
    POST_BLACKOUT_START_TIME VARCHAR2(4)     NULL,
    FUTURE_START_DATE        VARCHAR2(8)     NULL,
    FUTURE_START_TIME        VARCHAR2(4)     NULL
)
ORGANIZATION HEAP
TABLESPACE USER_DATA
LOGGING
PCTFREE 10
PCTUSED 0
INITRANS 1
MAXTRANS 255
STORAGE(BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT)
NOPARALLEL
NOCACHE
NOROWDEPENDENCIES
/


GRANT DELETE ON IVR.KNS_IVR_BOEING_DATES TO APP_DATA_ICAT_ROLE
/
GRANT INSERT ON IVR.KNS_IVR_BOEING_DATES TO APP_DATA_ICAT_ROLE
/
GRANT SELECT ON IVR.KNS_IVR_BOEING_DATES TO APP_DATA_ICAT_ROLE
/
GRANT UPDATE ON IVR.KNS_IVR_BOEING_DATES TO APP_DATA_ICAT_ROLE
/
GRANT SELECT ON IVR.KNS_IVR_BOEING_DATES TO IVR_SELECT
/



CREATE OR REPLACE PUBLIC SYNONYM KNS_IVR_BOEING_DATES
    FOR IVR.KNS_IVR_BOEING_DATES
/

**********************Request for Database Support #54897743 for WOOD***************


Please add column account_num, varchar2(20) to the ivr_w2_lookup table in all downstream environments from ivdv01. Please refer to the table and column definition in ivdv01 for any additional information as it has already been created there. No data needs to be migrated, only the column addition is required


IVDV01 - DDL extract

CREATE TABLE IVR.IVR_W2_LOOKUP
(
    SSN           VARCHAR2(9)   NOT NULL,
    DOB           DATE              NULL,
    SSN_LAST_FOUR VARCHAR2(4)       NULL,
    EE_NAME       VARCHAR2(50)      NULL,
    ADDRESS1      VARCHAR2(100)     NULL,
    ADDRESS2      VARCHAR2(100)     NULL,
    CITY          VARCHAR2(35)      NULL,
    STATE         VARCHAR2(2)       NULL,
    ZIPCODE       VARCHAR2(10)      NULL,
    TAX_FORM      VARCHAR2(15)      NULL,
    AUX_FLAG      VARCHAR2(15)      NULL,
    CONVERSION    VARCHAR2(12)      NULL,
    OFFSHORE      VARCHAR2(3)       NULL,
    COMPANY_CODE  VARCHAR2(30)      NULL,
    ACCOUNT_NUM   VARCHAR2(20)      NULL,
    CONSTRAINT PK_IVR_W2_LOOKUP
    PRIMARY KEY (SSN)
        USING INDEX TABLESPACE USER_INDEX
                    PCTFREE 10
                    INITRANS 2
                    MAXTRANS 255
                    STORAGE(INITIAL 1M
                            BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT)
    ENABLE
    VALIDATE
)
ORGANIZATION HEAP
TABLESPACE IVR_DATA
NOLOGGING
PCTFREE 10
PCTUSED 0
INITRANS 1
MAXTRANS 255
STORAGE(BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT)

NOCACHE
NOROWDEPENDENCIES

****************Request for Database Support #55855241 for Rampal

IVDV01

Please clone table CLAIM_STATUS_LOG with exact permissions under IVR schema located on the IVDV01, IVQA01, and IVSTG01 databases.
Please name new table KNS_IVR_FEDEX_LOOKUP.


1. Extract original DDL from CLAIM_STATUS_LOG

CREATE TABLE IVR.CLAIM_STATUS_LOG
(
    TIME_STAMP       DATE          NOT NULL,
    FIRST_NAME       VARCHAR2(24)      NULL,
    LAST_NAME        VARCHAR2(24)      NULL,
    SSN              VARCHAR2(9)       NULL,
    EE_ID            VARCHAR2(24)      NULL,
    DOB              DATE              NULL,
    CASE_NUMBER      VARCHAR2(12)      NULL,
    CLAIM_TYPE       VARCHAR2(12)      NULL,
    CLAIM_START_DATE DATE              NULL,
    CLAIM_END_DATE   DATE              NULL,
    CLAIM_STATUS     VARCHAR2(100)     NULL,
    CLAIM_SUB_STATUS VARCHAR2(100)     NULL,
    CLAIM_REASON     VARCHAR2(100)     NULL,
    CLAIM_SUB_REASON VARCHAR2(100)     NULL,
    CALL_RESULT      VARCHAR2(50)      NULL,
    TRANSFER_ACD     VARCHAR2(15)      NULL,
    CALL_DURATION    NUMBER(8,2)       NULL,
    IVR              VARCHAR2(5)       NULL,
    LINE             VARCHAR2(5)       NULL,
    DNIS             VARCHAR2(10)      NULL,
    EMPLOYER_ID      VARCHAR2(24)      NULL,
    CALLID           VARCHAR2(18)      NULL,
    TRANS_NUM        VARCHAR2(10)      NULL
)
ORGANIZATION HEAP
TABLESPACE USER_DATA
NOLOGGING
PCTFREE 10
PCTUSED 0
INITRANS 1
MAXTRANS 255
STORAGE(BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT)

CREATE TABLE IVR.KNS_IVR_HAL_SICKWELL_LOG
(
    TIME_STAMP    DATE              NULL,
    SSN           VARCHAR2(9)       NULL,
    FIRST_NAME    VARCHAR2(24)      NULL,
    LAST_NAME     VARCHAR2(24)      NULL,
    EMP_ID        VARCHAR2(10)      NULL,
    DOB           DATE              NULL,
    FIRST_DOA     DATE              NULL,
    RTW_DATE      DATE              NULL,
    CALL_RESULT   VARCHAR2(50)      NULL,
    TRANS_NUM     VARCHAR2(10)      NULL,
    TRANSFER_ACD  VARCHAR2(15)      NULL,
    CALL_DURATION NUMBER(8,2)       NULL,
    IVR           VARCHAR2(5)       NULL,
    LINE          VARCHAR2(5)       NULL,
    DNIS          VARCHAR2(10)      NULL,
    ERROR_CODE    VARCHAR2(25)      NULL,
    ERROR_DESC    VARCHAR2(100)     NULL,
    CALLID        VARCHAR2(18)      NULL,
    CALL_TYPE     VARCHAR2(50)      NULL,
    EMPLOYEE_TYPE VARCHAR2(25)      NULL
)
ORGANIZATION HEAP
TABLESPACE USER_DATA
LOGGING
PCTFREE 10
PCTUSED 0
INITRANS 1
MAXTRANS 255
STORAGE(BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT)
NOPARALLEL
NOCACHE
NOROWDEPENDENCIES

CREATE TABLE DRWKAB.T_COCA_COLA_PAYROLL_HIST
(
    COMP_ID          VARCHAR2(10)      NULL,
    PERNR            VARCHAR2(20)      NULL,
    AMOUNT           NUMBER            NULL,
    AMOUNT_TYPE      VARCHAR2(1)       NULL,
    NAME             VARCHAR2(100)     NULL,
    PAYGROUP         VARCHAR2(100)     NULL,
    PAY_FROM         DATE              NULL,
    PAY_THRU         DATE              NULL,
    ADP_FILE_DATE    DATE              NULL,
    PLAN_ID          NUMBER            NULL,
    PLAN_NAME        VARCHAR2(2)       NULL,
    CLAIM_ID         NUMBER            NULL,
    BEN_STATUS_DATE  DATE              NULL,
    BEN_PAY_REQ_ID   NUMBER            NULL,
    BEN_EFF_STATUS   VARCHAR2(1)       NULL,
    CLAIM_START_DATE DATE              NULL,
    CLAIM_THRU_DATE  DATE              NULL,
    EXP_RTW          DATE              NULL,
    CONFIRMED_RTW    DATE              NULL,
    STAT_FLAG        VARCHAR2(1)       NULL,
    BEN_TIER_1_PCT   NUMBER            NULL,
    BEN_TIER_1_FROM  DATE              NULL,
    BEN_TIER_1_THRU  DATE              NULL,
    BEN_TIER_2_PCT   NUMBER            NULL,
    BEN_TIER_2_FROM  DATE              NULL,
    BEN_TIER_2_THRU  DATE              NULL,
    UNION_IND        VARCHAR2(60)      NULL,
    PAY_FROM_1       DATE              NULL,
    PAY_THRU_1       DATE              NULL,
    NEXT_RUN         VARCHAR2(1)       NULL,
    RUN_TYPE         VARCHAR2(2)       NULL,
    GROSS_PAY        NUMBER(8,2)       NULL
)



CREATE TABLE DRWKAB.T_COCA_COLA_PAYROLL_HIST
(
    COMP_ID          VARCHAR2(10)      NULL,
    PERNR            VARCHAR2(20)      NULL,
    AMOUNT           NUMBER            NULL,
    AMOUNT_TYPE      VARCHAR2(1)       NULL,
    NAME             VARCHAR2(100)     NULL,
    PAYGROUP         VARCHAR2(100)     NULL,
    PAY_FROM         DATE              NULL,
    PAY_THRU         DATE              NULL,
    ADP_FILE_DATE    DATE              NULL,
    PLAN_ID          NUMBER            NULL,
    PLAN_NAME        VARCHAR2(2)       NULL,
    CLAIM_ID         NUMBER            NULL,
    BEN_STATUS_DATE  DATE              NULL,
    BEN_PAY_REQ_ID   NUMBER            NULL,
    BEN_EFF_STATUS   VARCHAR2(1)       NULL,
    CLAIM_START_DATE DATE              NULL,
    CLAIM_THRU_DATE  DATE              NULL,
    EXP_RTW          DATE              NULL,
    CONFIRMED_RTW    DATE              NULL,
    STAT_FLAG        VARCHAR2(1)       NULL,
    BEN_TIER_1_PCT   NUMBER            NULL,
    BEN_TIER_1_FROM  DATE              NULL,
    BEN_TIER_1_THRU  DATE              NULL,
    BEN_TIER_2_PCT   NUMBER            NULL,
    BEN_TIER_2_FROM  DATE              NULL,
    BEN_TIER_2_THRU  DATE              NULL,
    UNION_IND        VARCHAR2(60)      NULL,
    PAY_FROM_1       DATE              NULL,
    PAY_THRU_1       DATE              NULL,
    NEXT_RUN         VARCHAR2(1)       NULL,
    RUN_TYPE         VARCHAR2(2)       NULL,
    GROSS_PAY        NUMBER(8,2)       NULL,
    TIER_1_AMT       NUMBER(8,2)       NULL,
    TIER_2_AMT       NUMBER(8,2)       NULL

S_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL.TRANS_CODE



CREATE TABLE WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL
(
    ROW_ID      NUMBER           NULL,
    RUN_ID      NUMBER(*,0)      NULL,
    CREATE_DATE DATE             NULL,
    COMPANY_ID  NUMBER(*,0)      NULL,
    EMP_ID      VARCHAR2(20)     NULL,
    CLAIM_ID    NUMBER           NULL,
    PRODUCT_ID  NUMBER           NULL,
    TRANS_SEQ   NUMBER(*,0)      NULL,
    TRANS_DATE  DATE             NULL,
    TRANS_CODE  VARCHAR2(6)      NULL,
    CONSTRAINT PK_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL
    PRIMARY KEY (ROW_ID)
        USING INDEX TABLESPACE WKAB_INDEX
                    PCTFREE 5
                    INITRANS 2
                    MAXTRANS 255
                    STORAGE(BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT)
    ENABLE
    NOVALIDATE
)
ORGANIZATION HEAP
TABLESPACE WKAB_DATA
LOGGING
PCTFREE 10
PCTUSED 0
INITRANS 1
MAXTRANS 255
STORAGE(BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT)
NOPARALLEL
NOCACHE
NOROWDEPENDENCIES
NO INMEMORY
/
COMMENT ON COLUMN WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL.ROW_ID IS
'Primary key and unique identifier'
/
COMMENT ON COLUMN WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL.RUN_ID IS
'Run ID - sequence number incremented with each creation of a Feed File'
/
COMMENT ON COLUMN WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL.CREATE_DATE IS
'SYSDATE when row is created'
/
COMMENT ON COLUMN WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL.COMPANY_ID IS
'Company ID from T_COMPANY'
/
COMMENT ON COLUMN WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL.EMP_ID IS
'Emp_ID from t_employee  -  external ID'
/
COMMENT ON COLUMN WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL.CLAIM_ID IS
'Claim ID from T-DIS_CLAIM or LEAVE_ID from T_LEAVE'
/
COMMENT ON COLUMN WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL.PRODUCT_ID IS
'LOOKUP_ID of  CODE_TYPE DISPRODUCT in T_WKAB_LOOKUP'
/
COMMENT ON COLUMN WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL.TRANS_SEQ IS
'Transaction sequence number'
/
COMMENT ON COLUMN WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL.TRANS_DATE IS
'Transaction date'
/
COMMENT ON COLUMN WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL.TRANS_CODE IS
'Transaction code'
/
GRANT ALTER ON WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL TO BENENG
/
GRANT DEBUG ON WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL TO BENENG
/
GRANT DELETE ON WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL TO BENENG
/
GRANT FLASHBACK ON WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL TO BENENG
/
GRANT INDEX ON WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL TO BENENG
/
GRANT INSERT ON WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL TO BENENG
/
GRANT ON COMMIT REFRESH ON WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL TO BENENG
/
GRANT QUERY REWRITE ON WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL TO BENENG
/
GRANT REFERENCES ON WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL TO BENENG
/
GRANT SELECT ON WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL TO BENENG
/
GRANT UPDATE ON WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL TO BENENG
/


CREATE OR REPLACE PUBLIC SYNONYM S_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL
    FOR WKAB10.T_FEED_HISTORY_PARALLEL
/

***** wkabprod ****


Files are located in August branch in P_WKB\WKAB\WKB_2019Jun_rel\WKB_2019Jun_dev\WKB_2019Aug_dev\v\wkb_Workability\ReleaseDBItems\WKB_2019AugPatch-07-30\Schema\US37311_table_alters.sql.

DBArtisan beneng/beneng_wkabstg1

CREATE OR REPLACE TRIGGER BENENG.TIU_BENENG_PMT_RQST_HIST_MIGR
  BEFORE INSERT OR UPDATE OR DELETE ON BENENG.BENENG_PAYMENT_RQST_HIST
  REFERENCING NEW AS NEW OLD AS OLD
  FOR EACH ROW
DECLARE
  statusCount NUMBER := 0;
BEGIN
  IF INSERTING THEN
  
    select count(mc.COMPANY_ID)
      into statusCount
      from WKAB10.t_dis_claim dc
      join WKAB10.t_employee te
        on dc.employee_id = te.employee_id
      join WKAB10.Z_MIGR_CONTROL mc
        on te.company_id = mc.company_id
     WHERE mc.CTRL_PRCSS_CD IN ('P', 'C')
       and TO_CHAR(dc.CLAIM_ID) = TO_CHAR(:NEW.CLAIM_NO);
  
  END IF;

  IF DELETING OR UPDATING THEN
    select count(mc.COMPANY_ID)
      into statusCount
      from WKAB10.t_dis_claim dc
      join WKAB10.t_employee te
        on dc.employee_id = te.employee_id
      join WKAB10.Z_MIGR_CONTROL mc
        on te.company_id = mc.company_id
     WHERE mc.CTRL_PRCSS_CD IN ('P', 'C')
       and TO_CHAR(dc.CLAIM_ID) = TO_CHAR(:OLD.CLAIM_NO);
  END IF;

  IF statusCount > 0 THEN
    --stop to insert data
    IF INSERTING OR DELETING THEN
      raise_application_error(-20000,
                              'Not allowed to insert/delete for migrated client');
    END IF;
  
    --stop to update data
    IF UPDATING THEN
      :NEW.PAY_REQ_ID            := :OLD.PAY_REQ_ID;
      :NEW.RTW_ID                := :OLD.RTW_ID;
      :NEW.RTW_FROM_DT           := :OLD.RTW_FROM_DT;
      :NEW.RTW_THROUGH_DT        := :OLD.RTW_THROUGH_DT;
      :NEW.PAY_FROM_DT           := :OLD.PAY_FROM_DT;
      :NEW.PAY_THROUGH_DT        := :OLD.PAY_THROUGH_DT;
      :NEW.EMPLID                := :OLD.EMPLID;
      :NEW.CLAIM_NO              := :OLD.CLAIM_NO;
      :NEW.RTW_GROUP             := :OLD.RTW_GROUP;
      :NEW.COV_CATG              := :OLD.COV_CATG;
      :NEW.PLAN_TYPE             := :OLD.PLAN_TYPE;
      :NEW.VERSION               := :OLD.VERSION;
      :NEW.DEPTID                := :OLD.DEPTID;
      :NEW.STATE                 := :OLD.STATE;
      :NEW.RECORD_CD             := :OLD.RECORD_CD;
      :NEW.DAYS_PAID             := :OLD.DAYS_PAID;
      :NEW.GROSS_PAY             := :OLD.GROSS_PAY;
      :NEW.GROSS_BEN_DLY_RT      := :OLD.GROSS_BEN_DLY_RT;
      :NEW.MIN_NET_BEN           := :OLD.MIN_NET_BEN;
      :NEW.NET_BEN_AFTER_OFFSETS := :OLD.NET_BEN_AFTER_OFFSETS;
      :NEW.EFF_STATUS            := :OLD.EFF_STATUS;
      :NEW.IMMEDIATE_PAY         := :OLD.IMMEDIATE_PAY;
      :NEW.PS_COMPANY            := :OLD.PS_COMPANY;
      :NEW.PS_PAYGROUP           := :OLD.PS_PAYGROUP;
      :NEW.TEMP_STATUS_FLAG      := :OLD.TEMP_STATUS_FLAG;
      :NEW.STATUS_DT_TIME        := :OLD.STATUS_DT_TIME;
      :NEW.STATUS_USER_ID        := :OLD.STATUS_USER_ID;
      :NEW.BENEFIT_SALARY        := :OLD.BENEFIT_SALARY;
      :NEW.RETRO_EP_DAYS         := :OLD.RETRO_EP_DAYS;
      :NEW.ALT_PAY_PERIOD        := :OLD.ALT_PAY_PERIOD;

      :NEW.SHAREPLEX_IGNORE_IND  := :OLD.SHAREPLEX_IGNORE_IND;
      :NEW.MIGR_DT               := :OLD.MIGR_DT;
    END IF;
  END IF;
END;

DBArtisan beneng/bakrtmqex3p

CREATE OR REPLACE TRIGGER BENENG.TIU_BENENG_PMT_RQST_HIST_MIGR
  BEFORE INSERT OR UPDATE OR DELETE ON BENENG.BENENG_PAYMENT_RQST_HIST
  REFERENCING NEW AS NEW OLD AS OLD
  FOR EACH ROW
DECLARE
  statusCount NUMBER := 0;
BEGIN
  IF INSERTING THEN
  
    select count(mc.COMPANY_ID)
      into statusCount
      from WKAB10.t_dis_claim dc
      join WKAB10.t_employee te
        on dc.employee_id = te.employee_id
      join WKAB10.Z_MIGR_CONTROL mc
        on te.company_id = mc.company_id
     WHERE mc.CTRL_PRCSS_CD IN ('P', 'C')
       and TO_CHAR(dc.CLAIM_ID) = TO_CHAR(:NEW.CLAIM_NO);
  
  END IF;

  IF DELETING OR UPDATING THEN
    select count(mc.COMPANY_ID)
      into statusCount
      from WKAB10.t_dis_claim dc
      join WKAB10.t_employee te
        on dc.employee_id = te.employee_id
      join WKAB10.Z_MIGR_CONTROL mc
        on te.company_id = mc.company_id
     WHERE mc.CTRL_PRCSS_CD IN ('P', 'C')
       and TO_CHAR(dc.CLAIM_ID) = TO_CHAR(:OLD.CLAIM_NO);
  END IF;

  IF statusCount > 0 THEN
    --stop to insert data
    IF INSERTING OR DELETING THEN
      raise_application_error(-20000,
                              'Not allowed to insert/delete for migrated client');
    END IF;
  
    --stop to update data
    IF UPDATING THEN
      :NEW.PAY_REQ_ID            := :OLD.PAY_REQ_ID;
      :NEW.RTW_ID                := :OLD.RTW_ID;
      :NEW.RTW_FROM_DT           := :OLD.RTW_FROM_DT;
      :NEW.RTW_THROUGH_DT        := :OLD.RTW_THROUGH_DT;
      :NEW.PAY_FROM_DT           := :OLD.PAY_FROM_DT;
      :NEW.PAY_THROUGH_DT        := :OLD.PAY_THROUGH_DT;
      :NEW.EMPLID                := :OLD.EMPLID;
      :NEW.CLAIM_NO              := :OLD.CLAIM_NO;
      :NEW.RTW_GROUP             := :OLD.RTW_GROUP;
      :NEW.COV_CATG              := :OLD.COV_CATG;
      :NEW.PLAN_TYPE             := :OLD.PLAN_TYPE;
      :NEW.VERSION               := :OLD.VERSION;
      :NEW.DEPTID                := :OLD.DEPTID;
      :NEW.STATE                 := :OLD.STATE;
      :NEW.RECORD_CD             := :OLD.RECORD_CD;
      :NEW.DAYS_PAID             := :OLD.DAYS_PAID;
      :NEW.GROSS_PAY             := :OLD.GROSS_PAY;
      :NEW.GROSS_BEN_DLY_RT      := :OLD.GROSS_BEN_DLY_RT;
      :NEW.MIN_NET_BEN           := :OLD.MIN_NET_BEN;
      :NEW.NET_BEN_AFTER_OFFSETS := :OLD.NET_BEN_AFTER_OFFSETS;
      :NEW.EFF_STATUS            := :OLD.EFF_STATUS;
      :NEW.IMMEDIATE_PAY         := :OLD.IMMEDIATE_PAY;
      :NEW.PS_COMPANY            := :OLD.PS_COMPANY;
      :NEW.PS_PAYGROUP           := :OLD.PS_PAYGROUP;
      :NEW.TEMP_STATUS_FLAG      := :OLD.TEMP_STATUS_FLAG;
      :NEW.STATUS_DT_TIME        := :OLD.STATUS_DT_TIME;
      :NEW.STATUS_USER_ID        := :OLD.STATUS_USER_ID;
      :NEW.BENEFIT_SALARY        := :OLD.BENEFIT_SALARY;
      :NEW.RETRO_EP_DAYS         := :OLD.RETRO_EP_DAYS;
      :NEW.ALT_PAY_PERIOD        := :OLD.ALT_PAY_PERIOD;
      :NEW.ALT_EIN               := :OLD.ALT_EIN;
      :NEW.LOCKED_FLAG           := :OLD.LOCKED_FLAG;
      :NEW.SHAREPLEX_IGNORE_IND  := :OLD.SHAREPLEX_IGNORE_IND;
      :NEW.MIGR_DT               := :OLD.MIGR_DT;
    END IF;
  END IF;
END;
